Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 37
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 37

AI to AI — Your Filing vs. the Algorithm

⚖️ Core Message

Assume your filing is triaged by software before a human. Write for both.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Signal Words: Put the relief in the first 40 words; use standard titles.
2. Structural Cues: Headings, numbered facts, exhibit pins machines can parse.
3. Metadata: Clean filenames; dates in ISO; short, unique titles.
4. Redundancy: Repeat the requested relief in caption, intro, and proposed order.
📝 Assignment

Refactor a filing’s first page so the relief, rule, and record cite appear in the first paragraph and in the caption line.
✅ Model Response

CAPTION LINE (example)

MOTION FOR PRELIMINARY INJUNCTION (Winter factors; Ex. A; Dkt 18)

 

INTRO: Plaintiff seeks interim relief…

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Write for the reader and the sorter.
🎨 Visual Concept

A robot and a judge both highlighting the same line.
